<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226450/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="428" targetBox="[157,1429,199,978]" targetPageId="7">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1003,1056]" pageId="7" pageNumber="428">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,343,1003,1026]" pageId="7" pageNumber="428">FIGURES 14–15.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[352,578,1003,1025]" class="Insecta" family="Blephariceridae" genus="Blepharicera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="428" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hainana" status="sp.nov.">
<emphasis box="[352,578,1003,1025]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="428">Blepharicera hainana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[588,662,1004,1025]" pageId="7" pageNumber="428" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[588,662,1004,1025]" pageId="7" pageNumber="428">sp.nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
(male). 14: Genitalia, dorsal view. 15: Genitalia, ventral view. Scale bar: 14–15= 0.5 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1100,1809]" pageId="7" pageNumber="428">
Thoracic dorsum uniformly dark brown; pleuron brown; thorax without hairs. Legs brown, hairs on legs black. Wing (
<figureCitation box="[227,307,1136,1161]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 13" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1929,1952]" captionTargetBox="[362,1222,776,1908]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[348,1238,767,1908]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 13. Blepharicera hainana sp. nov. (male). 12: Habitus of male, lateral view; 13: Wing. Scale bar: 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226449/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="428">
Fig. 
<number box="[279,307,1137,1161]" pageId="7" pageNumber="428" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
) light brown, subhyaline; wing with obviously white net-like lines, veins brown. Sc rudimentary, not ending at base of Rs; Rs straight, as long as r-m; r-m straight. Base of halter dark brown, apex of halter black, with short black hairs.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1100,1809]" pageId="7" pageNumber="428">
Abdominal tergites mainly dark brown, tergites 
<number box="[760,802,1244,1269]" pageId="7" pageNumber="428" value="4.0" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="2.0">2–6</number>
with narrow yellow brown band basally, sternites dark brown; hairs on abdomen black. Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[690,827,1280,1305]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 15" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1003,1026]" captionTargetBox="[157,1429,199,978]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,193,982]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 15. Blepharicera hainana sp. nov. (male). 14: Genitalia, dorsal view. 15: Genitalia, ventral view. Scale bar: 14 – 15 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226450/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="428">
Figs. 
<number box="[753,827,1280,1305]" pageId="7" pageNumber="428" value="14.5" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="14.0">14–15</number>
</figureCitation>
): Epandrium semicircular, lateral and posterior margin rounded, posterior margin slightly concaved medially, with uniformly short hairs; hypandrium trapezoidal, posterior margin wavy, slightly concave medially, with short hairs laterally; cercus transverse, bilobate, each lobe elliptical, with dense patch of hairs apically; outer gonostylus forming a broad semicircular lobe medially, apical part finger-like, with uniformly hairs; inner gonostylus slender and curved; paramere transparent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1100,1809]" box="[199,418,1460,1485]" pageId="7" pageNumber="428">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,286,1460,1485]" pageId="7" pageNumber="428">Female</emphasis>
. Unknown.
</paragraph>
